724475f.text:
785-87 and 789 West End Avenue, west side, between 98th and 99th Streets, part of a block built in the mid 1890's. 789 and the remaining houses up to the corner of 99th Street will shortly be demolished for the erection of a 13-story apartment building, pictured in Underhill's view of that corner about 1915.
About 1912.
